<TITLE> Student arrested after Surja Sen Hall clash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 7 (bdnews24.com)Police raided Masterda Surja Sen Hall of Dhaka University early on Friday and arrested a student after a clash between two factions of Bangladesh Chhatra League on Thursday noon left 12 injured. "The hall was raided with the permission of the university authority from 2am to 3:50am," officer-in-charge of Shahbagh Police Station Rezaul Karim told bdnews24.com. "Rajib Farhad, a third-year student of international relations, was arrested as four rounds of bullets were recovered from his room." Karim said some machetes, iron bars, hockey sticks and sharp weapons were also recovered from the hall. The clash broke out between the supporters of president and general secretary of the hall unit of BCL, witnesses said. A private TV station said the BCL central committee suspended six over the incident. Proctor Saiful Islam Khan told bdnews24.com after the clash that a probe committee would be formed to identify the perpetrators. New BCL committees in 11 halls of the premier public university were formed on July 30 after seven years. bdnews
